==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|off|set}}, used to construct the noun form of the verb {{term|set off|to set off|lang=en}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|anchor|1}}Anything that acts as counterbalance; a [[compensating]] [[equivalent]].
#: ''Today's victory was an '''offset''' to yesterday's defeat.''
# {{context|anchor|2}}{{context|international trade}} A form of [[countertrade]] arrangement, in which the seller agrees to purchase within a set time frame products of a certain value from the buying country. This kind of agreement may be used in large international public sector contracts such as arms sales.
# {{context|anchor|3|obsolete|c. 1555}} A [[time]] at which something [[begin]]s; [[outset]].
# {{context|anchor|4}}A [[printing]] method, in which [[ink]] is carried from a metal [[plate]] to a rubber [[blanket]] and from there to the printing surface.
# {{context|anchor|5|programming}} The difference between a target memory address and a base address.
#: ''An array of bytes uses its index as the '''offset''', of words a multiple thereof.''
# {{context|anchor|6}}The [[distance]] by which one thing is out of [[alignment]] with another.
#: ''There is a small '''offset''' between the switch and the indicator which some users found confusing''.

